The paper deals with the spectral norm of Boolean functions, which is a concept commonly used in computational complexity theory. The paper also focuses on symmetric functions, which are a well-studied class of Boolean functions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves combinatorial techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper mentions applications to decision trees and communication complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
